net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.util

Class ComponentNameHelper

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.util.ComponentNameHelper

  • public final class ComponentNameHelper
extends Object
    Provides helper methods for identifying components by name and class in the component tree. Handles collisions by using an index which is assigned by the position in a breadth-first iteration of the tree.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • getQualifiedComponentNameAndClassMap

        public static Map<Object,List<Component>> getQualifiedComponentNameAndClassMap(Component root)
        Returns a map of component name and component Class objects to a List of Component objects. The keys are either String or Class objects. The value is a List with the Component objects in breadth first order.
        Parameters:
        root - The root of the component tree.
        Returns:
        Map.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if root is null.

      • getQualifiedComponentNameAndClassMap

        public static Map<Object,List<Component>> getQualifiedComponentNameAndClassMap(Component root,
                                                                               boolean requireVisible,
                                                                               boolean requireEnable)
        Returns a map of component name and component Class objects to a List of Component objects. The keys are either String or Class objects. The value is a List with the Component objects in breadth first order.
        Parameters:
        root - The root of the component tree.
        requireVisible - If true Component.isVisible() must return true for the component and any children to be considered.
        requireEnable - If true Component.isEnabled() must return true for the component and any children to be considered.
        Returns:
        Map.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if root is null.
